dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ukg1665702801028.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ukg1665702801028.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ukg1665702801028.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ukg1665702801028\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                                 \n Select Attributes\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Select data processing attributes for nodes in the DTD tree.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ukg1665702801028__p_d5876e1_d5877e1_d5878e1\">XML is typically used to define disconnected record sets. By selecting these attributes, you enable Uniface to reconnect disconnected occurrences, using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">reconnect</span> or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">retrieve/reconnect</span>\n</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ukg1665702801028__section_gfm_y1f_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d112345e62\">Fields</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ukg1665702801028__ul_rlp_y1f_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ukg1665702801028__li_d2957e1_d2958e1_d2959e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tbb1665702801175.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tbb1665702801175.html\" title=\"Determines whether the entity node in the DTD tree represents a disconnected record set. Valid values are True or False (default). It True, the Status, ID, and Checksum (CRC) properties are all set to True.\">Disconnected Record Set</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ukg1665702801028__li_d2960e1_d2961e1_d2962e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"udd1665702579942.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/udd1665702579942.html\" title=\"Determines whether the status data processing attribute is added for the selected entity node in the DTD tree. This attribute holds the occurrence modification state. It can be set or inspected using $occstatus. Valid values are True or False (default).\">Status</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ukg1665702801028__li_d2963e1_d2964e1_d2965e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dcy1665702801244.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dcy1665702801244.html\" title=\"Determines whether the id data processing attribute is added for the selected entity node in the DTD tree. The id holds the unique occurrence identifier and is generated the first time an occurrence is to a disconnected record set. Valid values are True or False (default).\">ID</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ukg1665702801028__li_d2966e1_d2967e1_d2968e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wpd1665702801317.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wpd1665702801317.html\" title=\"Determines whether the crc data processing attribute is added for the selected entity node in the DTD tree. CRC checksum values are produced by Uniface when loading data from a database, or when creating or loading data from XML streams. Valid values are True or False (default).\">Checksum (CRC)</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ukg1665702801028__li_d2969e1_d2970e1_d2971e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lrk1665702576500.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lrk1665702576500.html\" title=\"Determines whether the valerr data processing attribute is added for the selected entity node in the DTD tree. This attribute holds the occurrence or field validation error (depending on whether the selected item is an entity or field). Valid values are True or False (default).\">Validate</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ukg1665702801028__li_d2972e1_d2973e1_d2974e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pkb1665702801386.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pkb1665702801386.html\" title=\"Determines whether child nodes of the current entity in the DTD tree inherit the disconnected record set flags. Valid values are True or False (default).\">Apply to children</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qnx1665702574893.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>reconnect</a><p>Reconnect data loaded from a disconnected record set (XML, JSON, or Struct) with the occurrences in a component and database (if connected).</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/thr1665702690548.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>retrieve/reconnect</a><p>Reconnect data loaded from a disconnected record set (XML, JSON, or Struct) with the occurrences in a database or component.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8423489\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_8423489\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Select Attributes Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Select Attributes Select data processing attributes for nodes in the DTD tree. XML is typically used to define disconnected record sets. By selecting these attributes, you enable Uniface to reconnect disconnected occurrences, using reconnect or retrieve/reconnect Fields Disconnected Record Set Status ID Checksum (CRC) Validate Apply to children Related Links reconnect Reconnect data loaded from a disconnected record set (XML, JSON, or Struct) with the occurrences in a component and database (if connected). retrieve/reconnect Reconnect data loaded from a disconnected record set (XML, JSON, or Struct) with the occurrences in a database or component. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}